    "body": "```javascript\r\nfunction formatItemLabels($items) {\r\n    var $arr = Array();\r\n\r\n    $items.forEach(function($item, index) {\r\n        if($item.highlighted.includes(\"_\")) {\r\n            $keyValue = $item.highlighted.split('_');\r\n            $items[index].highlighted = $keyValue[1];\r\n            $arr[$keyValue[0]] = $item;\r\n        }\r\n    });\r\n    return $arr;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nOn taking a close look at the `formatItemLabels` from the `jsfilddle`, It seems like you are changing the position of the data in the array(` $arr[$keyValue[0]] = $item;`)\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2019-10-16 22-02-41](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25791025/66939441-b2df0e00-f060-11e9-9556-3bc308235091.png)\r\n\r\nYou are splitting data from `highlighted` property and adding the `item` to the first value from the split",
